## PB3(1/5): captured-resource audit fix.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 29 (PB3 design checkpoint): a closure capture
## (`+sig` / `~sig` / `<sig` for a resource-typed value) is OWNED
## by the closure ENV, not by the body's invocation. A retained
## closure (`*Closure()`) may be invoked multiple times; if the
## body could move, drop, return, or store-bare the capture, the
## second invocation would be UAF (the slot was consumed by the
## first call).
##
## The ownership pass rejects `-cap` (drop) on a captured resource
## with the unified `rejectNonConsumableBindingOp` helper —
## parallel to M20i.1's loop-borrow rejection. Diagnostic wording
## branches on which flag fired so the user sees a context-
## appropriate explanation.
##
## Sample triggers covered by this audit (non-exhaustive):
##   `-sig`     drop captured resource
##   `<sig`     move captured resource
##   `return sig`  return captured resource (would-be smuggle)
##   `f(sig)`   bare alias pass as call arg
##   `x = sig`  bare alias as binding RHS

sub main()
  sig: *Signal(Int) = *Signal(value: 0)
  bump = |+sig|
    -sig
  bump()
